{"products":[{"id":15857536205173,"title":"The Three sisters May Bundle","handle":"three-sisters-may-bundle","body_html":"\u003cp\u003eThe bundle we’ve decided on this month is the 3 sisters bundle with mixed sunflowers and Russian Scorzonera thrown in for good measure; Scorzonera being a perennial root crop- survival food that requires minimal effort once its it. \u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGolden Bantam Sweet corn, Lazy house wife beans and Spaghetti Squash, all complimenting each others growing.- Companion plants..\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e Corn, beans and squash were traditionally grown together as main agricultural crops by indigenous peoples of Central and North America. Sunflowers were added on the north edges of their gardens like a\"fourth sister”. The birds and the bees will love you for it! \u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe maize and beans are planted together in mounds and around the base of the plants grow the squash .The corns makes for a trellis for the climbing beans. The beans are nitrogen fixing via nodules under ground and apparently that helps to stabalize the corn crop in high winds. The wide leaves of the squash plant shade the ground acting as a living mulch keeping the soil moist and help to slow down the weeds.\u003c\/p\u003e","published_at":"2026-04-29T13:20:19+01:00","created_at":"2026-04-22T16:23:07+01:00","updated_at":"2026-05-12T21:44:32+01:00","vendor":"Brown Envelope Seeds","product_type":"bundle","tags":["Big gift boxes","gift boxes","Small gift boxes"],"variants":[{"id":57093359075701,"title":"Default Title","option1":"Default Title","option2":null,"option3":null,"sku":"NoWWBPT","requires_shipping":true,"taxable":true,"featured_image":null,"available":true,"price":"12.00","grams":66,"compare_at_price":null,"position":2,"product_id":15857536205173,"created_at":"2026-04-22T16:23:07+01:00","updated_at":"2026-05-12T21:44:32+01:00"}],"images":[{"id":82347911086453,"created_at":"2026-04-22T16:15:24+01:00","position":1,"updated_at":"2026-04-22T16:15:30+01:00","product_id":15857536205173,"variant_ids":[],"src":"https:\/\/cdn.shopify.com\/s\/files\/1\/0510\/9065\/3376\/files\/image_6e861eb1-2754-4190-b1c0-dd76e0da3cbe.jpg?v=1776870930","width":2304,"height":2978}],"options":[{"name":"Title","position":1,"values":["Default Title"]}]},{"id":15856685482357,"title":"Job’s tears\/ Adlay","handle":"ezeer-thresh-wheat-copy","body_html":"\u003cp\u003e\u003cmeta charset=\"UTF-8\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eJob's Tears, Adlay (Coix lacryma-jobi var. ma-yuen), the shiny, thin shelled version of Job’s tears, the bead grass. We got this from our friend Radix and it has been growing happily in the tunnel for several years. I put a clump of it outside where it seemed to survive the winter, but then I asked someone to clear out the bed and I don't know where it went. Anyway the seeds are germinating quite \u003c\/span\u003ewell. so we are offering a few packets. Allegedly really nutritious and even medicinal. \u003cmeta charset=\"UTF-8\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eThe seed contains about 52% starch, 18% protein, 7% fat. \u003c\/span\u003e\u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAverage 20 seeds per packet \u003c\/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e \u003c\/p\u003e","published_at":"2026-04-21T16:01:38+01:00","created_at":"2026-04-21T15:52:00+01:00","updated_at":"2026-05-12T21:44:32+01:00","vendor":"Brown Envelope Seeds","product_type":"","tags":["Cereals","Perennial"],"variants":[{"id":57090206761333,"title":"Default Title","option1":"Default Title","option2":null,"option3":null,"sku":"3","requires_shipping":true,"taxable":true,"featured_image":null,"available":true,"price":"3.00","grams":4,"compare_at_price":null,"position":1,"product_id":15856685482357,"created_at":"2026-04-21T15:52:00+01:00","updated_at":"2026-05-12T21:44:32+01:00"}],"images":[{"id":82311664599413,"created_at":"2026-04-21T16:01:03+01:00","position":1,"updated_at":"2026-04-21T16:01:08+01:00","product_id":15856685482357,"variant_ids":[],"src":"https:\/\/cdn.shopify.com\/s\/files\/